<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
There are fighters (me) and there are lovers (hippies) and then there are the people caught in the middle.  I of course will have to play on the PVP servers because I love the idea but without the merchants and politicians I might as well go play an FPS because it will turn out to be the same thing.<P>Option #1: Have zones, like cities, where you CANNOT kill other players.  This will drop some options (like bank robbery, store robbery, assassination of politicians, etc) but the "non-twitch" gamers will be able to do their own thing in safety.  To have an econmy that works have resources that must be harvested in PVP zones this way you are adding in the ability to become a pirate.  To keep everyone from becoming a pirate have the government of the planet suply them with a gun turret if they decide to become a farmer or miner.  Once they make money they buy more turrets and their operation expands.<P>Option #2: Have all zones PVP but certain player classes (or profesiions if you choose) cannot be killed.  While this eliminates pirates the game is still entertaining and somewhat realistic.<P>Option #3 (THE PREMIUM PLAN): Make all zones PVP.  Fighting in towns will cause guards to come unless in an enclosed area (like I shoot a sotre owner in hte closet).  To keep the economy going and to have a system of player-led government you are given priveledges. Politicians get a body guard, merchants get surveillance cameras (which alert law enforcement agencies), the merchants get escorts, farmers and miners get gun turrets.  This gives the maximum realism level and opens up an entirely new game.<P>While not everyone likes this Verant has been known to open up a variety of servers.  you could have one of each servers and everyone is happy.  If they see that not everyone likes a particular server they may shut it down after the first few months.
</FONT>
